{"title_page": "Cindy Rakowitz", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Cindy Rakowitz\n| image       = Cindy Rakowitz.jpg\n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = Cindy Plaut\n| birth_date  = <!-- {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| birth_place = [[Plattsburgh (city), New York|Plattsburgh, New York]]\n| residence   =\t[[Los Angeles, California]]\n| alma_mater  =\t[[Queens College]], [[City University of New York]]\n| home_town   =\t[[Queens, New York]]\n| known_for   = Division President for [[Playboy Enterprises]] (1986&ndash;2001)\n| boards      = United States Global Enterprise Association\n| awards      = Luminaire Award - Women in Production<ref name=\"Luminaire\">{{cite web | title = Luminaire Archive Bios - Luminaire Award Recipients | author =  | publisher =  | date =  | url = http://partnershipinprintproduction.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=69&Itemid=117 | accessdate = December 14, 2010 }}{{Dead link|date=July 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><br/>3 [[Clio Awards]] on behalf of Playboy for excellence in advertising<br/>13 Mercury Awards<ref>{{cite web | title =Cindy Rakowitz | author=  | publisher = | date =  | url = http://www.linkedin.com/in/cindyrakowitz | accessdate = December 14, 2010}}</ref>\n| website     = {{url|http://www.brpublicrelations.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Cindy Rakowitz''' is an American executive, known as a public relations expert and as a former Division President for [[Playboy Enterprises]], where she ran international public relations, marketing and advertising, as well as the modeling agency for over 15 years.\n\n==Playboy==\nBetween the years 1986 and 2001, Cindy Rakowitz managed Playboy's policies in the fields of public relations, marketing and advertising, also representing the company as spokesperson in relation to the major media outlets. She was involved in the development of Playboy brand and its related trademarks and logos,<ref>{{cite web | title = 'Millennium' inspires thousands of trademark gimmicks | author=  | publisher = [[Sarasota Herald-Tribune]] | date = February 9, 1998 | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=pb0cAAAAIBAJ&sjid=f30EAAAAIBAJ&pg=4655,6274549&dq=cindy-rakowitz&hl=en | accessdate = November 9, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Patterns | author= Amy M. Spindler | publisher = [[The New York Times]] | date = March 29, 1994 | url = http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F4061EF73D5B0C7A8EDDAA0894DC494D81 | accessdate = November 9, 2010}}</ref> she advised the celebrities who had a relationship with Playboy,<ref name=\"People & Places\">{{cite web | title = People & Places | author=  | publisher = [[Spartanburg Herald-Journal]] | date = February 2, 1996 | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=PbQeAAAAIBAJ&sjid=WM8EAAAAIBAJ&pg=4034,165235&dq=cindy-rakowitz&hl=en | accessdate = November 9, 2010}}</ref> voiced Playboy's views on various issues<ref name=\"People & Places\"/><ref>{{cite web | title = Hef in a huff | author=  | publisher = [[Salon.com]] | date = August 11, 2000 | url = http://www.salon.com/news/politics/feature/2000/08/11/sanchez | accessdate = November 23, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Romanian Playboy Article Draws Protests | author= Alex Kuczynski | publisher = [[The New York Times]] | date = April 24, 2000 | url = http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F60D17FD3F540C778EDDAD0894D8404482 | accessdate = November 9, 2010}}</ref> and produced Playboy's major events.<ref>{{cite web | title = Beach party or forum? | author= Steven Barrie-Anthony | publisher = [[Los Angeles Times]] | date = August 25, 2003 | url = https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/388501591.html?dids=388501591:388501591&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Aug+25%2C+2003&author=Steven+Barrie-Anthony&pub=Los+Angeles+Times&desc=STYLE+%26+CULTURE%3B+SOCIAL+CLIMES%3B+Beach+party+or+forum%3F%3B+It%27s+a+night+of+bikini+babes+and+speechifying+as+gubernatorial+candidates+and+the+media+check+out+Jim+%27Poorman%27+Trenton%27s+%27Governor%27s+Ball.%27&pqatl=google | accessdate = November 9, 2010}}</ref> Cindy worked on a daily basis with Playboy founder [[Hugh M. Hefner]],<ref name=\"BR\">{{cite web | title = Cindy Rakowitz | author=  | publisher = BR Public Relations | date = | url = http://www.brpublicrelations.com/team.html#CindyRakowitz | accessdate = November 23, 2010}}</ref> in the strategic planning of his [[Playboy Mansion|Mansion]] parties and representing him as a spokesperson.<ref>{{cite web | title = The Shandling Show Hits a Nasty Episode | author= George Rush and Joanna Molloy with Marcus Baram | work = [[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]] | date =January 19, 1998 | url = http://www.nydailynews.com/archives/gossip/1998/01/19/1998-01-19_the_shandling_show_hits_a_na.html | accessdate = November 23, 2010}}</ref>\n\nShe served on the board of the Playboy Foundation and became involved in AIDS research and education (she helped and supported [[Rebekka Armstrong]] when she came out as HIV-positive and became one of the best-known public faces of heterosexual HIV transmission).<ref>{{cite web | title = Some Like It Hot | author= Helen Eisenbach | publisher = [[POZ (magazine)|POZ]] | date =June 1998| url =http://www.poz.com/articles/228_1616.shtml| accessdate = December 14, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = A Bunny's Life | author= Susan Forrest | publisher = The Body | date = November 1999 | url = http://www.thebody.com/content/art32594.html | accessdate = December 14, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = HIV positive Playmate thanks Cindy Rakowitz  | author= | publisher = | date = | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7vMe7j1CTbI | accessdate = December 14, 2010}}</ref>\n\nConsidering an independent career, Cindy Rakowitz left the company in 2001, after negotiating the terms of a four-month notice. It was at that time that the internet became a popular vehicle for adult entertainment and Playboy began providing these users with harder core sexual programming.<ref>{{cite web | title = Playboy Goes Xxx| author=Kevin Peraino | publisher = [[Newsweek]] | date =July 16, 2001| url = http://www.newsweek.com/2001/07/15/playboy-goes-xxx.html | accessdate = December 14, 2010}}</ref>\n\n==BR Public Relations==\n\nAfter leaving Playboy Enterprises, Cindy Rakowitz started her own media and entertainment company in Los Angeles, named RNR Entertainment, then she co-founded, together with Diane Blackman, Blackman Rakowitz Public Relations (known as BR Public Relations). She planned and executed brand strategies for major companies, establishing luxury brands, like [[Patr\u00f3n]] tequila or Dermalogica skincare. In Patr\u00f3n tequila's case, the media strategy changed perceptions about tequila, producing positive media coverage after securing endorsements from celebrities like [[Jamie Foxx]] and [[Kevin Costner]] or after featuring it as the choice of [[Tom Cruise]]'s character in ''[[Vanilla Sky]]''.<ref>{{cite web| title = BR Public Relations - Case Studies| url = http://www.brpublicrelations.com/casestudies.html| accessdate = December 14, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101115183511/http://www.brpublicrelations.com/casestudies.html| archive-date = November 15, 2010| url-status = dead}}</ref>\n\n==Media==\n\nCindy Rakowitz hosts ''Stars of PR'' on VoiceAmerica Radio, a live weekly radio program devoted to public relations and marketing.<ref>{{cite web| title = Stars of PR, with Cindy Rakowitz| publisher = VoiceAmerica| url = http://www.voiceamerica.com/voiceamerica/vshow.aspx?sid=971| accessdate = November 23, 2010| archive-url = https://archive.is/20120917192755/http://www.voiceamerica.com/voiceamerica/vshow.aspx?sid=971| archive-date = September 17, 2012| url-status = dead}}</ref> She appears in other media as a public relations consultant, with opinions about the image of various public figures.<ref>{{cite web | title = What's A-Rod Worth To The Yankees Now?| author= | publisher = [[Forbes]] | date = February 9, 2009| url = https://www.forbes.com/2009/02/09/alex-rodriguez-arod-yankees-steroids-0209_arod.html| accessdate = November 23, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = The Most Disliked People In Sports| author= | publisher = [[Forbes]]| date = July 28, 2009| url = https://www.forbes.com/2009/07/28/the-most-disliked-people-in-sports-business-sports-disliked.html| accessdate = November 23, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Tiger Woods parmi les athl\u00e8tes... impopulaires| author= | publisher = [[Canadian Online Explorer]] | date =June 30, 2010| url = http://fr.canoe.ca/cgi-bin/imprimer.cgi?id=692076| accessdate = November 23, 2010}}</ref> As a media trainer, she is known for her ability to advise her clients how to deal with the press during unanticipated crises.<ref name=\"BR\"/><ref>{{cite web | title = Irak - La guerra de las im\u00e1genes| author=Paula Lugones | publisher = [[Clar\u00edn (Argentine newspaper)|Clar\u00edn]] | date =| url = http://edant.clarin.com/diario/2004/05/17/elmundo/i-01615.htm | accessdate = November 23, 2010}}</ref> She received certification from Harvard Law's Disputes Program in 1993.<ref name=\"Luminaire\"/>\n\nShe is involved in [[social media]] advocacy, as a speaker on marketing through social media platforms<ref>{{cite web | title = L.A. Therapist Update| author= | publisher =  | date = September\u2013October 2010| url = http://lacamft.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/LA-CAMFT-Sept-Oct-2010-Newsletter.pdf | accessdate = December 14, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title = AAMFT-CA| url = http://www.aamftca.org/main/main_nesm.html| accessdate = December 14, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101114142500/http://www.aamftca.org/main/main_nesm.html| archive-date = November 14, 2010| url-status = dead}}</ref> and as the editor of ProVisors' newsletter ''Trusted Advisor''.<ref>{{cite web | title = Trusted Advisor Newsletter| author= | publisher = ProVisors | date =| url = http://archive.constantcontact.com/fs049/1103031757159/archive/1103414589465.html | accessdate = December 14, 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Writer==\n\nIn 2012, she published ''Emergency Public Relations: Crisis Management In a 3.0 World'' (co-authored with Alan B. Bernstein), a book on [[crisis management]] issues and rapid responses to [[public relation]] emergencies.<ref>{{cite web | title = ''Emergency Public Relations: Crisis Management In a 3.0 World''| author=Alan B. Bernstein and Cindy Rakowitz | publisher =  | date =| url = http://emergencypublicrelations.com/| accessdate = March 3, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Fit 4 The Cause==\n\nCindy Rakowitz initiated ''Fit 4 The Cause'', a [[Thousand Oaks, California|Thousand Oaks]] based non-profit organization raising funds for health related causes through group fitness programs performed in unexpected venues, such as malls, parks, corporate suites, hotels, rooftops and health clubs.<ref>{{cite web | title = Fit 4 The Cause| author=| publisher =  | date =| url = http://www.fit4thecause.org/| accessdate = May 22, 2014}}</ref> Until 2012, she participated in group exercise programs as a hobby, then she became more interested in the fitness lifestyle and its effects on physical and mental well-being. In February 2013, she was licensed by the American Counsel on Exercise certification and began working as a Group Fitness Instructor.<ref>{{cite web | title = Cindy Rakowitz - Wellness, Health and Fitness| author=| publisher =  | date =| url = http://www.brpublicrelations.com/services/wellness-health-and-fitness/| accessdate = May 22, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.brpublicrelations.com/team.html#CindyRakowitz Profile at BR Public Relations]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rakowitz, Cindy}}\n[[Category:American public relations people]]\n[[Category:Playboy people]]\n[[Category:Queens College, City University of New York alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Cindy Rakowitz\n| image       = Cindy Rakowitz.jpg\n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = Cindy Plaut\n| birth_date  = <!-- {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| birth_place = [[Plattsburgh (city), New York|Plattsburgh, New York]]\n| residence   =\t[[Los Angeles, California]]\n| alma_mater  =\t[[Queens College]], [[City University of New York]]\n| home_town   =\t[[Queens, New York]]\n| known_for   = Division President for [[Playboy Enterprises]] (1986&ndash;2001)\n| boards      = United States Global Enterprise Association\n| awards      = Luminaire Award - Women in Production<ref name=\"Luminaire\">{{cite web | title = Luminaire Archive Bios - Luminaire Award Recipients | author =  | publisher =  | date =  | url = http://partnershipinprintproduction.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=69&Itemid=117 | accessdate = December 14, 2010 }}{{Dead link|date=July 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><br/>3 [[Clio Awards]] on behalf of Playboy for excellence in advertising<br/>13 Mercury Awards<ref>{{cite web | title =Cindy Rakowitz | author=  | publisher = | date =  | url = http://www.linkedin.com/in/cindyrakowitz | accessdate = December 14, 2010}}</ref>\n| website     = {{url|http://www.brpublicrelations.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Cindy Rakowitz''' is an American executive, known as a public relations expert and as a former Division President for [[Playboy Enterprises]], where she ran international public relations, marketing and advertising, as well as the modeling agency for over 15 years.\n\n==Playboy==\nBetween the years 1986 and 2001, Cindy Rakowitz managed Playboy's policies in the fields of public relations, marketing and advertising, also representing the company as spokesperson in relation to the major media outlets. She was involved in the development of Playboy brand and its related trademarks and logos,<ref>{{cite web | title = 'Millennium' inspires thousands of trademark gimmicks | author=  | publisher = [[Sarasota Herald-Tribune]] | date = February 9, 1998 | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=pb0cAAAAIBAJ&sjid=f30EAAAAIBAJ&pg=4655,6274549&dq=cindy-rakowitz&hl=en | accessdate = November 9, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Patterns | author= Amy M. Spindler | publisher = [[The New York Times]] | date = March 29, 1994 | url = http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F4061EF73D5B0C7A8EDDAA0894DC494D81 | accessdate = November 9, 2010}}</ref> she advised the celebrities who had a relationship with Playboy,<ref name=\"People & Places\">{{cite web | title = People & Places | author=  | publisher = [[Spartanburg Herald-Journal]] | date = February 2, 1996 | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=PbQeAAAAIBAJ&sjid=WM8EAAAAIBAJ&pg=4034,165235&dq=cindy-rakowitz&hl=en | accessdate = November 9, 2010}}</ref> voiced Playboy's views on various issues<ref name=\"People & Places\"/><ref>{{cite web | title = Hef in a huff | author=  | publisher = [[Salon.com]] | date = August 11, 2000 | url = http://www.salon.com/news/politics/feature/2000/08/11/sanchez | accessdate = November 23, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Romanian Playboy Article Draws Protests | author= Alex Kuczynski | publisher = [[The New York Times]] | date = April 24, 2000 | url = http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F60D17FD3F540C778EDDAD0894D8404482 | accessdate = November 9, 2010}}</ref> and produced Playboy's major events.<ref>{{cite web | title = Beach party or forum? | author= Steven Barrie-Anthony | publisher = [[Los Angeles Times]] | date = August 25, 2003 | url = https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/388501591.html?dids=388501591:388501591&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Aug+25%2C+2003&author=Steven+Barrie-Anthony&pub=Los+Angeles+Times&desc=STYLE+%26+CULTURE%3B+SOCIAL+CLIMES%3B+Beach+party+or+forum%3F%3B+It%27s+a+night+of+bikini+babes+and+speechifying+as+gubernatorial+candidates+and+the+media+check+out+Jim+%27Poorman%27+Trenton%27s+%27Governor%27s+Ball.%27&pqatl=google | accessdate =