publisher = [[Newsweek]] | date =July 16, 2001| url = http://www.newsweek.com/2001/07/15/playboy-goes-xxx.html | accessdate = December 14, 2010}}</ref>\n\n==BR Public Relations==\n\nAfter leaving Playboy Enterprises, Cindy Rakowitz started her own media and entertainment company in Los Angeles, named RNR Entertainment, then she co-founded, together with Diane Blackman, Blackman Rakowitz Public Relations (known as BR Public Relations). She planned and executed brand strategies for major companies, establishing luxury brands, like [[Patr\u00f3n]] tequila or Dermalogica skincare. In Patr\u00f3n tequila's case, the media strategy changed perceptions about tequila, producing positive media coverage after securing endorsements from celebrities like [[Jamie Foxx]] and [[Kevin Costner]] or after featuring it as the choice of [[Tom Cruise]]'s character in ''[[Vanilla Sky]]''.<ref>{{cite web| title = BR Public Relations - Case Studies| url = http://www.brpublicrelations.com/casestudies.html| accessdate = December 14, 2010| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101115183511/http://www.brpublicrelations.com/casestudies.html| archive-date = November 15, 2010| url-status = dead}}</ref>\n\n==Media==\n\nCindy Rakowitz hosts ''Stars of PR'' on VoiceAmerica Radio, a live weekly radio program devoted to public relations and marketing.<ref>{{cite web| title = Stars of PR, with Cindy Rakowitz| publisher = VoiceAmerica| url = http://www.voiceamerica.com/voiceamerica/vshow.aspx?sid=971| accessdate = November 23, 2010| archive-url = https://archive.is/20120917192755/http://www.voiceamerica.com/voiceamerica/vshow.aspx?sid=971| archive-date = September 17, 2012| url-status = dead}}</ref> She appears in other media as a public relations consultant, with opinions about the image of various public figures.<ref>{{cite web | title = What's A-Rod Worth To The Yankees Now?| author= | publisher = [[Forbes]] | date = February 9, 2009| url = https://www.forbes.com/2009/02/09/alex-rodriguez-arod-