{"title_page": "On the Run II Tour", "text_new": "{{short description|Beyonc\u00e9 and Jay-Z concert tour}}\n{{Infobox concert\n| concert_tour_name = On the Run II Tour \n| image             = On the Run II Tour poster.jpg\n| image_size        = 200\n| artist            = [[Beyonc\u00e9]] and [[Jay-Z]]\n| album            =  ''[[Everything Is Love]]''\n| start_date        = {{Start date|2018|6|6}}\n| end_date          = October 4, 2018\n| number_of_legs    = 2\n| number_of_shows   = 48\n| attendance        = 2.170 million\n| gross             = $253.5 million\n| Misc              = {{Extra tour chronology\n | Group            = [[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n | Type             = tour\n | Last tour        = [[The Formation World Tour]]<br />(2016)\n | This tour        = '''On the Run II Tour'''<br />(2018)\n | Next tour        = \n}}\n\n{{Extra tour chronology\n | Group            = [[Jay-Z]]\n | Type             = tour\n | Last tour        = [[4:44 Tour]]<br />(2017)\n | This tour        = '''On the Run II Tour'''<br />(2018)\n | Next tour        = \n}}\n{{Extra tour chronology\n | Group            = [[The Carters]]\n | Type             = tour\n | Last tour        = [[On the Run Tour (Beyonc\u00e9 and Jay-Z)|On the Run Tour]]<br />(2014)\n | This tour        = '''On the Run II Tour'''<br />(2018)\n | Next tour        = \n}}\n}}\nThe '''On the Run II Tour'''<ref name=Tour>{{cite web|url=http://www.beyonce.com/tour|title=On the Run II Tour|publisher=beyonce.com|date=March 12, 2018|accessdate=March 13, 2018}}</ref> was the second co-headlining stadium [[concert tour|tour]] by American singer [[Beyonc\u00e9]] and rapper [[Jay-Z]]. The tour was officially announced on March 12, 2018, and began on June 6, 2018 in [[Cardiff]]. It concluded on October 4, 2018 in [[Seattle]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/music/news/jay-z-and-beyonce-announce-on-the-run-ii-stadium-tour-dates-1202723972/amp/|title=\nJay-Z and Beyonce Announce \u2018On the Run II\u2019 Stadium Tour Dates|date=March 12, 2018|accessdate=March 13, 2018}}</ref> This is their first tour together since [[On the Run Tour (Beyonc\u00e9 and Jay-Z)|On the Run Tour]] in 2014.\n\nOn May 31, it was announced via [[Twitter]] that R&B duo [[Chloe x Halle]] and [[DJ Khaled]] would be the opening acts for the North American leg of the tour.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thehollywoodunlocked.com/chloe-x-halle-dj-khaled-open-beyonce-jay-zs-otr2-tour/|title=Chloe x Halle & DJ Khaled Set To Open Beyonc\u00e9 & JAY-Z's On The Run II Tour|website=thehollywoodunlocked.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-01}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the show in [[London]] on June 16, 2018, the pair released their collaborative album ''[[Everything Is Love]]'' exclusively on [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]. The news of the duo's new album was announced by a showing of the music video for its lead single, \"[[Apeshit]]\", followed by a sign on stage which announced \"ALBUM OUT NOW\u201d. The release was then shared on the artists' respective [[Instagram]] and [[Facebook]] profiles with the artist of the album being dubbed as The Carters. On the same day, the music video for \"Apeshit\", was released on Beyonc\u00e9's official [[YouTube]] channel.\n\n==Commercial performance==\n[[File:Beyonce in Rome 1.jpg|thumb|left|Beyonc\u00e9 performing at the tour.]]\n''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' stated the tour could double the [[On the Run Tour (Beyonc\u00e9 and Jay-Z)|On the Run Tour]]'s gross, predicting it could gross between $180&nbsp;million and $200&nbsp;million, if the success of the previous tour is replicated.<ref>{{cite magazine|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8240747/beyonce-jay-z-on-the-run-ii-tour-double-business-2014-tour|title=Beyonc\u00e9 and JAY-Z's On The Run II Tour Could Do Double the Business Their 2014 Tour Did|date=March 12, 2018|access-date=March 13, 2018}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the first day of general sale, an extra show was added in [[Amsterdam]], after the first date sold out within an hour,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nu.nl/muziek/5185334/beyonce-en-jay-z-geven-extra-concert-in-amsterdam.amp|title=Beyonc\u00e9 en Jay-Z geven extra concert in Amsterdam|date=March 20, 2018|access-date=March 21, 2018}}</ref> as well as in [[Paris]], [[Landover, Maryland|Landover]], [[East Rutherford, New Jersey|East Rutherford]], [[Chicago]], [[Atlanta]], [[Houston]], [[Pasadena, California|Pasadena]] and [[London]]. Newly added shows were also announced on March 20, in [[Columbus, Ohio|Columbus]], [[Columbia, South Carolina|Columbia]], [[Seattle]], and [[London]].<ref>{{cite magazine|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/columns/hip-hop/8254566/beyonce-jay-z-on-the-run-ii-tour-new-dates|title=JAY-Z & Beyonc\u00e9 Announce Additional Dates for On the Run II Tour|date=March 20, 2018|access-date=March 21, 2018}}</ref>\n\nBillboard ranked On the Run II Tour as the 3rd-[[List of highest-grossing concert tours|highest-grossing tour]] of the year, selling over 2,177,049 tickets and grossing over $253&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"gross\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8488851/touring-charts-year-ed-sheeran-tops-taylor-swift-beyonce |title=The Year in Touring Charts: Ed Sheeran Claims 2018's Top Tour; Taylor Swift, Beyonc\u00e9 & Jay-Z Do Big Business |last=Eric|first=Frankenberg |date=December 5, 2018 |work=Billboard |accessdate=December 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Critical response==\n[[File:Beyonce in Rome.jpg|thumb|Beyonc\u00e9 in Rome]]\nThe opening show in Cardiff received positive reviews. Mark Sutherland from ''Rolling Stone'' gave the opening show in Cardiff a positive review. He called it a sort of reaffirmation of dominance for the pair as they deliver a \"a hits-packed, visually stunning show\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/how-beyonce-is-asserting-her-dominance-at-on-the-run-ii-w521221|title=5 Ways Beyonce Is Asserting Her Dominance at the 'On the Run II' Tour|work=Rolling Stone|first=Brittany|last=Spanos|date=June 7, 2018|accessdate=June 9, 2018}}</ref> Writing for ''The Guardian'', Rachel Aroesti awarded the concert four out of five stars and noted that the concept of the show revolved around the singers showing the \"deathless nature of their love rather than its perfection\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/jun/07/beyonce-jay-z-otr-ii-tour-review-opening-night-cardiff|title=Beyonc\u00e9 & Jay-Z: OTR II review \u2013 heart-stopping scenes from a marriage|first=Rachel|last=Aroesti|date=June 7, 2018|accessdate=June 9, 2018}}</ref> Beyonc\u00e9 was critiqued after some of her \"biggest hits\" were left out of the set list on the opening night, including \"[[Halo (Beyonc\u00e9 song)|Halo]]\" and \"[[Single Ladies (Put a Ring on It)]]\". However, with over 60 songs rehearsed for the tour, the set list was believed to change between shows.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-44384522|title=Beyonce and Jay-Z loved-up as tour begins|last=Savage|first=Mark|date=2018-06-07|work=BBC News|access-date=2018-06-10|language=en-GB}}</ref>\nBonginkosi Tshabalala of ''No Name'' publications added that the show at Houston proved that \"no matter what happens LOVE wins\".\n\n==Set list==\n{{hidden\n| headercss = background: #CECEF2; font-size: 100%; width: 75%;\n| contentcss = text-align: left; font-size: 100%; width: 95%;\n| header = Europe\n| content = This set list is representative of the June 6 show in Cardiff, Wales.\n{{div col}}\n#<li value=1> \"[[Holy Grail (Jay-Z song)|Holy Grail]]\" \n#\"[[Part II (On the Run)]]\"\n#\"[['03 Bonnie & Clyde]]\" \n#\"[[Drunk in Love]]\"\n#\"[[Diva (Beyonc\u00e9 song)|Diva]]\" / \"[[Irreplaceable]]\" / \"Everybody Mad\"\n#\"[[Clique (song)|Clique]]\"\n#\"[[Dirt off Your Shoulder]]\"\n#\"[[On to the Next One]]\"\n#\"[[FuckWithMeYouKnowIGotIt]]\" / \"[[Flawless (Beyonc\u00e9 song)|Flawles