.htm] USNS Arrowhead (T-AGSE-4)\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Military Sealift Command ships]]\n* {{commonscat-inline}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authoritycontrol}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Arrowhead (T-AGSE-4)}}\n[[Category:Auxiliary ships of the United States Navy]]\n[[Category:2009 ships]]\n\n{{Black Powder class submarine escort ships}}\n{{US-mil-ship-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=June 2019}}\n\n{|{{Infobox ship begin}}\n{{Infobox ship image\n|Ship image=MV_HOS_Arrowhead_(7985812230).jpg\n|Ship caption=\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Hide header=\n|Ship country=\n|Ship flag={{USN flag}}\n|Ship name=USNS Arrowhead\n|Ship namesake=\n|Ship ordered=\n|Ship builder=[[Leevec Industries]], [[Jennings, Louisiana]]\n|Ship laid down=\n|Ship launched=2009\n|Ship operator=[[Military Sealift Command]]\n|Ship acquired=\n|Ship commissioned=\n|Ship decommissioned=\n|Ship in service=\n|Ship out of service=\n|Ship struck=\n|Ship homeport=\n|Ship reinstated=\n|Ship identification=*{{IMO Number|9472373}}\n*{{MMSI Number|338092000}}\n*[[Maritime call sign|Callsign]]:  NARR\n|Ship honors=\n|Ship fate=\n|Ship status=Active\n|Ship notes=\n}}\n{{Infobox ship characteristics\n|Hide header=\n|Header caption=\n|Ship class=Submarine and Special Warfare Support Vessels\n|Ship displacement=\n|Ship length={{convert|250|ft|m|abbr=on}}\n|Ship beam={{convert|54|ft|m|abbr=on}}\n|Ship draft={{convert|15|ft|m|abbr=on}}\n|Ship propulsion=Diesel\n|Ship speed={{convert|14|kn}}\n|Ship range=\n|Ship complement=\n|Ship sensors=\n|Ship EW=\n|Ship armament=*2 \u00d7 [[M242 Bushmaster#Mk 38 Mod 2|Mk 38 Mod 2]] 25 mm autocannon<ref>{{cite book |author1=Ken W. Sayers |title=U.S. Navy Auxiliary Vessels: A History and Directory from World War I to Today |isbn=978-1-4766-7256-4}}</ref>\n*Crew-served [[Browning M2 machine gun]]s\n|Ship armour=\n|Ship armor=\n|Ship aircraft=\n|Ship notes=\n}}\n|}\n\n'''USNS ''Arrowhead'' (T-AGSE-4)''' is a submarine support vessel acquired by the [[U.S. Navy]] in 2015 